http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Resolutions-passed/article14000516.ece

Resolutions were passed at a function to mark the 97th birthday of veteran journalist Patil Puttappa here on Thursday.They included demand for setting up a committee comprising a Cabinet Minister and a bureaucrat for liaisoning with the Union government and the riparian States for resolving the Mahadayi dispute; short-term programmes to improve infrastructure related to health, education and power and long-term programmes for ensuring economic development; improving connectivity and industrial development; and setting up a system to bring to book the corrupt.